sections.body:
The connection string passed to the driver must use exact hostnames for
the servers, as set in the [Replica Set Config](manual/reference/replica-configuration).
Given the following configuration settings for your replica set, in
order for the replica set discovery and [failover](manual/reference/glossary) to work, the driver must have access
to `server1`, `server2`, and `server3`.

```JSON
{
  "_id": "testSet",
  "version": 1,
  "protocolVersion": 1,
  "members": [
    {
      "_id": 1,
      "host": "server1:31000"
    },
    {
      "_id": 2,
      "host": "server2:31001"
    },
    {
      "_id": 3,
      "host": "server3:31002"
    }
  ]
}
```
